### Responsive Height Handling:

```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .container {
    height: 100vh;
  }

  .scrollableContent {
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
  }
}
```

### Fixed Elements Handling:

```css
/* Fixed Test Buttons */
.fixedTestButtons {
  position: fixed;
  bottom: 1.5rem;
  right: 1.5rem;
  z-index: 1000;
}

/* Fixed Header */
.header {
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
  z-index: 100;
}
```

### MUST DO:

- **ALWAYS** use `height: 100vh` for page containers
- **ALWAYS** prevent content from exceeding viewport height
- **ALWAYS** separate scrollable areas from fixed elements
- **ALWAYS** use flexbox for vertical layout management
- **ALWAYS** apply height constraints consistently across all devices

### NEVER DO:

- ‚ùå Create layouts that exceed viewport height
- ‚ùå Allow content to overflow without proper scroll areas
- ‚ùå Use arbitrary height values instead of viewport units
- ‚ùå Ignore height constraints on mobile devices

